).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,618,2013]" box="[199,572,1914,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,394,1914,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Biological notes.</emphasis>
Host unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,618,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the Atlantic Forest, the main biome in the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1196,1358,1951,1977]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, where the 
<typeStatus box="[192,240,1987,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="50">type</typeStatus>
material was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
